I was about five or six the first time I heard my mom say, &ldquo;I&rsquo;m glad I won&rsquo;t be around to see it.&rdquo; I didn&rsquo;t understand what she was saying. Nonetheless, it felt ominous and unsettling. I let it go.
I&rsquo;m not sure when I heard it the second time, phrased slightly differenlty: &ldquo;I won&rsquo;t be alive when . . . .&rdquo;
I don&rsquo;t remember what the &ldquo;when&rdquo; was. It didn&rsquo;t matter.
